 of the pastry, cut a cross and fold back its corners to create a small opening. Set aside. Spread mushrooms in pastry-lined tart tin."},{"content":"Place reserved cooked garlic, eggs, flour and crème fraîche in mixing bowl and cook <b>5 min\/80°C\/speed 2<b>, then blend <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"Pour sauce over mushrooms, cover pie with second pastry disc, seal well around the edges, brush pie surface with milk and bake for 30-35 minutes (200°C), or until golden brown. Serve hot or warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Combine button mushrooms with other mushroom varieties (e.g. porcini, chanterelles, crimini, portobello, morels, shiitake)."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","1h 30m","6 portions"]}